   {:e #blake3 "cb1ab5870740736ae860882ea5333cd72f6abb7419ce68442275b54f8e2585d2" :a :harvest/accomplishments :v "AMBIENT RECONCILIATION — ARCHITECTURE: Three components. (1) TRACE PRODUCER: In main.rs, after commands::run() returns CommandOutput, extract spec refs from the JSON via parse_spec_refs on stringified JSON values. For each ref, query AVET index for all entities also referencing that spec element. Write :recon/trace datom with top-3 related entities + spec-neighborhood ID. Cost: ~100μs (AVET is O(1)), ~50 bytes per trace datom. Runs on EVERY command, not just observe. (2) CONCENTRATION DETECTOR: In guidance.rs, add spec_neighborhood_concentration(store, recent_txns: usize) -> Vec<ConcentrationSignal>. Scans :recon/trace datoms from last N transactions. Groups by spec-neighborhood. If any neighborhood has 3+ traces → fires signal with the neighborhood's related entities. (3) GUIDANCE INTEGRATION: Wire concentration signals into methodology_gaps() as a new gap type: 'spec_concentration'. When active, braid status shows: 'concentration: 5 recent commands touch INV-INTERFACE-001 — 11 existing tasks in this neighborhood'. This makes the signal visible through the existing guidance pipeline without new UI.; AMBIENT RECONCILIATION — GRAPH TRAVERSAL DESIGN: The structural similarity dimension uses the spec graph (entities connected by :spec/traces-to, :task/traces-to, :impl/implements edges). Algorithm for spec_graph_neighbors(store, spec_refs: &[String]) -> Vec<(EntityId, f64)>: (1) For each spec ref string, resolve to EntityId via AVET index on :element/id. (2) For each resolved spec entity, find ALL other entities that reference it: query VAET index (reverse ref lookup) for entities pointing TO this spec entity via :task/traces-to or :impl/implements. (3) Score each neighbor by 1.0 / (1 + hop_count). Direct reference = 1.0, 1-hop neighbor = 0.5. (4) Deduplicate: if an entity appears via multiple paths, take max score. (5) Filter: exclude self, exclude entities already in the command output. This is a BFS of depth 2 on the spec graph, using existing VAET index for O(1) reverse-ref lookup. No new indexes needed. The VAET index was built for exactly this purpose (spec/01-store.md: 'reverse reference traversal'). For popular spec refs (INV-STORE-001 referenced by 50+ entities), apply inverse document frequency weighting: score *= 1/log(ref_count) to penalize ubiquitous refs.; AMBIENT RECONCILIATION — INTERACTION WITH EXISTING WORK: This EPIC interacts with 4 existing EPICs. (1) RECON-SPEC-GRAPH (t-827dbbb8): The graph traversal component of ambient reconciliation SUBSUMES this task — spec_graph_neighbors is a superset of what RECON-SPEC-GRAPH proposed. Close t-827dbbb8 when AR-2 is done. (2) CRB-9 (t-c9782a1a, pluggable reconciliation sources): Ambient reconciliation is the BUILT-IN source; CRB-9 adds external sources (cass, cm). They compose — the trace producer runs built-in graph traversal AND invokes external sources if registered. (3) Reflexive Divergence EPIC (t-cf728d6d): The phantom INV-GUIDANCE-024/025 is a reflexive divergence instance — the system's model of its specs doesn't match the actual spec files. AR-1 (crystallize phantom specs) is a prerequisite. (4) Zero-Cost Methodology EPIC (t-e2e64fe4): The trace producer IS zero-cost observation — reconciliation as a side-effect of every command, not a separate action. AR-2 directly implements the 'observation as side-effect' principle.; AMBIENT RECONCILIATION — SPEC PREREQUISITE: INV-GUIDANCE-024 and INV-GUIDANCE-025 are referenced by 6 tasks but DO NOT EXIST as formal spec elements. They are phantom references — tasks trace to nonexistent specs. This breaks C5 (Traceability) and means the structural dimension of reconciliation would fail for these tasks (no spec entity to traverse through). Must crystallize INV-GUIDANCE-024 (Knowledge Reconciliation Completeness) and INV-GUIDANCE-025 (Reconciliation Gate Threshold) as formal spec elements BEFORE implementing the graph traversal. Additionally, INV-STORE-014 (Every Command Is a Transaction) already mandates that every command produces a transaction — the :recon/trace datom is a natural extension of this invariant. The trace IS the observation that INV-STORE-014 requires for read commands.; AMBIENT RECONCILIATION — VERIFICATION AND COMPOUNDING: Verification has 3 layers. (1) Proptest: for any entity E with spec refs R, spec_graph_neighbors(store, R) returns only entities that share at least one ref in R (no false positives). (2) Regression test: create store with ACP EPIC (traces to INV-INTERFACE-001) and TSV task (traces to INV-INTERFACE-001). Run braid task create for TSV. Verify :recon/trace datom includes ACP EPIC. This is the EXACT failure mode that triggered this analysis. (3) E2E script: e2e_ambient_reconciliation.sh — create spec elements, tasks tracing to them, run 5 commands in same neighborhood, verify braid status shows concentration warning. Compounding: every command adds a trace datom. After 100 commands per session × 30 sessions = 3000 trace datoms. The concentration detector has full visibility into which spec neighborhoods are hot. This is the self-improvement loop (SEED.md S7) applied to reconciliation — the system learns which areas of the spec are being actively worked on and surfaces connections automatically. The trace data also feeds the R(t) routing system: tasks in concentrated neighborhoods get a contention_boost because the agent is already in that conceptual space.; AMBIENT RECONCILIATION — ROOT CAUSE: The reconciliation failure (TSV/CTP tasks created without surfacing ACP overlap) has a deeper root than wrong similarity function. The root is: reconciliation only runs when the agent explicitly asks for it (via braid observe). But the agent went straight from analysis to task creation, bypassing the reconciliation gate entirely. 10+ tasks created before catching the overlap. The fix is not better similarity — it is making reconciliation a FIELD the agent exists in, not a GATE it passes through. Every braid command already loads the store and produces JSON output. Adding a reconciliation trace as a side-effect datom means: after computing output, extract spec refs from the JSON, run 2-hop spec-graph traversal, append top-3 related entities as :recon/trace datom. This is ZERO-COST to the agent (invisible unless asked) but creates a persistent, queryable record of what the system knew was related at every action. The trace accumulates — after 5 commands in the same spec neighborhood, the guidance system surfaces it as a methodology gap: 'spec-neighborhood concentration detected'.\nSession entity: :task/t-a5be3c81; Session entity: :task/t-248ded4d; Session entity: :task/t-abf64b39; Session entity: :task/t-051b88f6; Session entity: :task/t-62d2e8f2; Session entity: :task/t-a8d013a1" :op :assert}
